---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../lib/constants';
---

<Layout title={`DMCA Policy | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={`DMCA copyright infringement policy for ${SITE_TITLE}. Read how to submit copyright concerns or takedown requests.`}>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16 max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold mb-2 tracking-tight">DMCA Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-foreground/50 mb-10">Last updated: July 5, 2026</p>

    <Card padding="lg" class="space-y-6 text-foreground/80 leading-relaxed text-sm">
      <p>
        <strong class="text-foreground">{SITE_TITLE}</strong> respects the intellectual property rights of others and expects its users to do the same. In accordance with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act of 1998 ("DMCA"), we will respond expeditiously to claims of copyright infringement committed using our website that are reported to our designated contact below.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-foreground pt-4">1. DMCA Notice of Infringement</h2>
      <p>
        If you are a copyright owner, or authorized to act on behalf of one, please report alleged copyright infringements taking place on or through the website by sending a written notice to our contact email below.
      </p>
      <p>
        Upon receipt of a valid notice, we will take whatever action, in our sole discretion, we deem appropriate, including removal of the challenged material from the website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-foreground pt-4">2. Requirements for a DMCA Notice</h2>
      <p>
        To file a notice of infringement, you must provide a written communication (via email) that includes substantially the following:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3">
        <li><strong>Signature:</strong> A physical or electronic signature of a person authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed.</li>
        <li><strong>Identification of the Copyrighted Work:</strong> Identification of the copyrighted work claimed to have been infringed.</li>
        <li><strong>Identification of the Infringing Material:</strong> The specific URL/link of the page containing the material, and information reasonably sufficient to permit us to locate it.</li>
        <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> An address, telephone number, and/or email address at which you may be contacted.</li>
        <li><strong>Good Faith Statement:</strong> A statement that you have a good faith belief that use of the material in the manner complained of is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.</li>
        <li><strong>Accuracy Statement:</strong> A statement, under penalty of perjury, that the information in the notification is accurate and that you are authorized to act on behalf of the owner.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-foreground pt-4">3. Where to Send Your Notice</h2>
      <p>
        All DMCA notices must be sent via email:
      </p>
      <div class="rounded-xl p-6 bg-black/4 dark:bg-white/5 border border-black/10 dark:border-white/10 my-4">
        <p class="font-semibold text-foreground">Copyright Contact Email:</p>
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`} class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline font-mono">{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
        <p class="text-xs text-foreground/50 mt-2">Please state "DMCA Takedown Request" in the subject line of your email for prioritized processing.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-foreground pt-4">4. Counter-Notification Procedure</h2>
      <p>
        If you believe material you own or are authorized to act on behalf of was removed by mistake or misidentification, you may file a counter-notification with us containing:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Your physical or electronic signature.</li>
        <li>Identification of the material removed and its location before removal.</li>
        <li>A statement under penalty of perjury that you have a good faith belief the material was removed as a result of mistake or misidentification.</li>
        <li>Your name, address, telephone number, and a statement consenting to the jurisdiction of the relevant Federal District Court.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-foreground pt-4">5. Repeat Infringers</h2>
      <p>
        Since {SITE_TITLE} does not require registration or support user accounts, we do not maintain a register of active user accounts. However, we reserve the right to block access or restrict IP addresses of repeat infringers to protect intellectual property rights.
      </p>
    </Card>
  </div>
</Layout>
